properties.name: Paradise Falls
properties.description: Paradise Falls is a converted strip style shopping mall turned slaver haven in the Capital Wasteland, with business ties to further slave trade in The Pitt. It is a constant source of fear for many of the wasteland denizens.

properties.name: Vault 12
properties.description: In order to study the effects of radiation on the selected population, the Vault door was designed not to close properly. This is the Necropolis vault and a large population of ghouls was the result.

properties.name: Vault 15
properties.description: Intended to stay closed for 50 years and include people of radically diverse ideologies. Vault 15 is also the birthplace of three raider groups, the Khans, Jackals, and Vipers, and Shady Sands, which would become the New California Republic

properties.name: Toxic Caves
properties.description: The toxic caves are north of Klamath. Before the War, it was a military warehouse of some sort. Now, it's a radioactive cave inhabited by geckos (little and gold, though mostly gold).

properties.name: NCR Bazaar
properties.description: The NCR Bazaar is the marketplace just outside of the New California Republic capital, Shady Sands in 2241.

properties.name: Phoenix
properties.description: Phoenix is a location mentioned by Joshua Graham. He describes it as "justplace,metalandstone".

properties.name: Flagstaff
properties.description: Flagstaff is the capital of Caesar's Legion, In 2255, the ruins of the city were taken over by Caesar's Legion who christened it as their new capital.

properties.name: Sunnyvale
properties.description: Sunnyvale is where the platinum chip was developed for Mr. House, which was to be hand-delivered to Mr. House on October 23, 2077. However, due to the Great War, the chip was lost among the destruction.

properties.name: Sac-Town
properties.description: Sacramento, the former capital of California, is now a lawless, uncontrolled city. In the region northeast of Sacramento, a gang called the 80s can often be found.

properties.name: Rattletail
properties.description: It was founded by New California Republic settlers who had moved into Baja, sometime between 2256 and 2261. According to Hanlon the village was nothing more than six shacks built around a well.

properties.name: Blackfoot
properties.description: The Blackfoot tribe is a tribe from the former Arizona. It was the first of the tribes that Caesar took control of and forged into his Caesar's Legion.

properties.name: Two Sun
properties.description: Two Sun is all that's left of the Arizona city of Tucson. Raul Tejada claims to have lived there for 75 years after the bombs fell, but left before the arrival of Caesar's Legion.

properties.name: Malpais
properties.description: Malpais is a settlement located somewhere in New Mexico. It is mentioned by Corporal Sterling during dialogue about his capture by Caesar's Legion.

properties.name: Sloan
properties.description:
A small community for the miners that work at
Quarry Junction.

properties.name: Quarry Junction
properties.description: A large stone quarry with a Deathclaw infestation

properties.name: Temple of the Union
properties.description: The Temple of the Union is a small compound of escaped slaves who wish to create a haven to protect and inspire all runaway slaves.

properties.name: Lost Hills
properties.description: The Lost Hills is a pre-War government bunker and the headquarters of the Brotherhood of Steel. Mysterious and impenetrable, it is the subject of myths and legends among many wastelanders.

properties.name: Saugus Ironworks
properties.description: Saugus is a large ironworks facility formally controled by a gang of raiders known as the Forged

properties.name: Dunwich Borers
properties.description: A large, functioning mine formally controlled by raiders.

properties.name: Secret Vault
properties.description: A secret vault dedicated to protect high-members of Vault-Tec Industries and used to research the latest technologies (like electrical laser weapons and instant regeneration) and the Forced Evolutionary Virus.

properties.name: Turtledove Detention Camp
properties.description: Turtledove Detention Camp (or Camp Turtledove)[1] is a military prison camp located in Point Lookout.

properties.name: The Squat
properties.description: A grouping of tents, small buildings and some trees up against the side of a cliff. There are squatters wandering the area.

properties.name: One Pine
properties.description: One Pine is a settlement mentioned by President Aaron Kimball in his speech at the Hoover Dam. In his speech, he refers to the home of Jeremy Watson, who was "borninatinshackontheoutskirtsofOnePine".

properties.name: Caliente
properties.description: Caliente is a small town based in a volcanic basin lying north of the Mojave Wasteland, on Highway 93. It has a stable source of fresh water and a geothermal power station, making it a popular target for raiders, typically White Legs or the 80s.

properties.name: The Citadel
properties.description: The Citadel is the heavily defended headquarters of the Brotherhood of Steel in the Capital Wasteland in 2277. It is built into and beneath the ruins of the Pentagon, the pre-war headquarters of the U.S. military.

properties.name: Arefu
properties.description: Arefu is a small Capital Wasteland settlement consisting of four houses, located on top of a crumbling overpass bridge.

properties.name: Big Town
properties.description: Big Town is a medium sized settlement surrounded by a makeshift wall. The town consists of six survivors and four possible additional characters. The town has been ravaged by super mutant and slaver attacks.

properties.name: Little Lamplight
properties.description: Little Lamplight is a pre-War underground cavern tourist attraction made into a settlement in the Capital Wasteland, run and populated entirely by children under the age of 16.

properties.name: Canterbury Commons
properties.description: Canterbury Commons is a trading post and a small town located on the eastern edge of the Capital Wasteland. Canterbury Commons was initially founded by Uncle Roe and his sister Daisy as a trading center for caravan merchants in the Capital Wasteland.

properties.name: Adams AFB
properties.description: Adams Air Force Base is a heavily-fortified Enclave compound outside the Capital Wasteland in Maryland.  After the Battle of Adams Air Force Base, the Brotherhood of Steel occupy the base.

properties.name: Far Harbor
properties.description: Far Harbor is a harbor town in the Fallout 4 add-on Far Harbor. It is home to the harbormen and women, a settlement well defended against The Island's wild creatures and one of the last not consumed by the Fog.

properties.name: Great Lanta
properties.description: It was invaded by slavers at one point. However, one slave group led by a man named Ehren was disbanded by Ehran himself, and the slaves were freed.

properties.name: Erie Stretch
properties.description: The Erie Stretch is a region mentioned by the slave Brand in The Pitt.Most likely referring to an area where Lake Erie is.

properties.name: Junction City
properties.description: Junction City is a mid sized town in Kansas that refused to form an alliance with the Brotherhood of Steel. Their independent posture was reinforced by their victory over one of the Calculator's humanoid robots.

properties.name: Coldwater
properties.description: Cold Water is a town built amongst the ruins of the pre-War city of Coldwater, Kansas. Cold Water is mainly famous in the region for its casino, and is inhabited by mostly humans, as well as a few ghouls.

properties.name: Big MT
properties.description: The Big Mountain Research and Development Center, alternately known as Big MT or the Big Empty, was a privately owned pre-War defense contractor and research centre.

properties.name: Menkey Butte Mine
properties.description: The Menkey Butte Mine was originally a silver mine, now disused it may still contain something of value.

properties.name: Newton
properties.description: Newton or Junk City was the main camp of the Reaver Movement, a technology-worshiping cult.

properties.name: Freeport
properties.description: Before the war, it was a moderately sized city in the state of llinois. By 2197, the town had become a rather large raider den, housing limited supplies of fossil fuels and a large alcohol distillery.

properties.name: Bunker Gamma
properties.description: After the Brotherhood defeated the psychic Beastlords, they moved south to this bunker to establish a secure area of operations.

properties.name: Ulysses' Temple
properties.description: It is the home of Ulysses, and his shrine to the Old World. The "Temple" is the biggest nuclear silo of the Divide, capable of launching several nuclear missiles at once.

properties.name: Osceolla
properties.description: Osceolla was the main base of operations of Gammorin's (Paladin Latham's) super mutant army. It was a military compound constructed near the place where part of the Brotherhood of Steel Air Convoy crashed.

properties.name: Jefferson
properties.description: The rubble-strewn city of Jefferson is what remains of Jefferson City, Missouri. One of Gammorin's super mutant staging areas was located there. The mutants had a semi-permanent military base in the ruins of Jefferson.

properties.name: Vault 87
properties.description: Vault 87 is one of the vault series of fallout shelters developed by Vault-Tec. It is the birthplace of the super mutants and centaurs in the Capital Wasteland.

properties.name: Galaxy News Radio
properties.description: Galaxy News Radio is a building in Washington, D.C. It is home to the radio broadcast of the same name, and also functions as a Brotherhood of Steel base.

properties.name: Bloomfield Space Center
properties.description: Bloomfield Space Center is an old Air Force base, littered with the rusting carcasses of numerous air vehicles. It has two working space shuttles, and houses a gang called the Rusty Hooks, whose hideout is in the shuttle launch pad.

properties.name: Devil's Graveyard
properties.description: Formally a raider stronghold. After the raiders attacked the village of Dirt Haven, which were allied with the Brotherhood of Steel, the Brotherhood pacified this area by destroying local raider forces.

properties.name: St. Louis
properties.description: The ruins of a once large city, plagued by Super Mutants and raider gangs.

properties.name: Kansas City
properties.description: The Ruins of Kansas city was a Gammorin's Army base. It also composed of another ghoul town in its center, independent of the Gammorin's Army named Gravestone.

properties.name: Sentinel Site
properties.description: The Sentinel site was a pre-War military facility that was working to make the air-dropped 'Mk. 28' nuclear bombs compatible with a newer ICBM delivery system.

properties.name: Owen's Lake
properties.description: The dry lakebed of Owens Lake was the staging ground for many raider attacks throughout the Sierra Nevada region of California, and attacks were commonplace until New Californian soldiers arrived in the region driving out any raider tribes.

properties.name: The Arch and Dove Cathedral
properties.description: Before the Great War a small community sprung up around a cathedral. Post-war its home to a rather devout religious cult who has a tendency to be a refuge for runaway teens.

properties.name: The Sacred Bog
properties.description: The sacred bog is a location in Point Lookout, reached via the sacred bog entrance on the westernmost side of the map. It is a winding path through the swamp, populated by various swamp creatures.

properties.name: Pilgrims Landing
properties.description: Pilgrim's Landing is a small tourist attraction inhabited by Panada, Tobar the Ferryman and Nadine. It is the closest thing to actual civilization in Point Lookout.

properties.name: Calvert Mansion
properties.description: The Calvert Mansion is a large Victorian mansion located in Point Lookout. It is inhabited by Desmond Lockheart, a 200 year-old ghoul from before the Great War.

properties.name: Point Lookout Lighthouse
properties.description: The Point Lookout Lighthouse is a location in Point Lookout. It is a cylindrical structure containing both the main lighthouse facility as well as a secret basement. It is abandoned when first encountered but can come to be inhabited by smugglers.

properties.name: Vault 70
properties.description: All jumpsuit extruders fail after six months. Most of the inhabitants were Mormons. The city of New Canaan was founded by the vault dwellers after they left the vault.

properties.name: LA Vault
properties.description: The Vault-Tec demonstration vault. It was not part of the experiment, and was the Master's vault under the Cathedral in Fallout 1. Located in Southern LA

properties.name: Vault 13
properties.description: Vault 13 is one of a series of fallout shelters developed by Vault-Tec in southern California beneath Mt. Whitney. It is located west of Shady Sands and Vault 15, and east of Mariposa Military Base. It was the home of the Vault Dweller.

properties.name: Greyditch
properties.description: Grayditch is a neighborhood located on the outskirts of the Washington, D.C. ruins, south of the Super-Duper Mart. It was ravaged by "thosemonsters" according to Bryan Wilks, which are later revealed to be fire ants, in 2277.

properties.name: Unnamed community
properties.description: Marge LeBarge from Fallout two was born here. "BorninCanada,ontheedgeofLakeLaberge,sheisaburlymiddle-agedwomanwith.."

properties.name: Anchorage
properties.description: In the winter of 2066, Anchorage was taken over by China. The Anchorage Front Line became a battleground. On January 10, 2077, the United States took back Anchorage and began its counter-invasion of China.

properties.name: Spanish Fork National Guard Armoury
properties.description: Under the guidance of Ulysses the White Legs raided the Armoury and acquired their signature 'Storm Drums' guns.

properties.name: Brotherhood Montana Bunker
properties.description: "AbranchbasedinalargebunkerexistsinMontana,andasof2277isledbyanElderPatrocolus." Exact location not known.                                          http://fallout.wikia.com/wiki/Brotherhood_of_Steel#Montana_Brotherhood

properties.name: Mount Hood
properties.description:
Mount Hood is a location in Oregon in Fallout Extreme.
Not much is known about this location, except that several settlements are located around the mountain.

properties.name: Issaquah
properties.description:
The Issaquah Nation is a post-War country.
They rebuilt the town of Issaquah, Washington,. The Issaquah Nation was to appear in the canceled Fallout Extreme.

properties.name: Mount Saint Helens
properties.description: Not much is known about this place, except that the mountain can be explored to find Vault 6, which has been cleverly hidden underneath the mountain. A Brotherhood Of Steel experimentation lab is seen here as well.

properties.name: Troll Warren
properties.description: Troll Warren is a city in Fallout:Extreme. This city of super mutants was taken over by The Cause.

properties.name: Montauk Preserve
properties.description: Not much is known about this location, except that it plays a part in the plot of Fallout Extreme's first chapter, and belongs to the Montauk.

properties.name: Kodiak Base
properties.description: Not much is known about this location, except that it plays a part in the plot of Fallout Extreme's first chapter.

properties.name: Fort Willamette
properties.description: Fort Willamette is a Brotherhood of Steel base in northwestern Oregon. The Cause was to destroy the base to continue their swing up through the continental US and into Alaska.

properties.name: Canyon City
properties.description: Canyon City was a town near the Kansas-Colorado border, where the Calculator set up robot repair station 10.92 around 2198. It is in this station that damaged robots were mended and parts of destroyed robots were rebuilt and combined to form a whole.

properties.name: The Farmhouse
properties.description:
The farmhouse is a crop farm with a house in the Texas Wasteland.
South of the truck stop the farmhouse is owned by Fey and consists of one small map. The garden yields giant corn and vegetables and has become infested with Texas Rattlers.

properties.name: Acadia
properties.description: Acadia is a former observatory, used by DiMA as a safe haven for synths on the Island in 2287.

properties.name: The Nucleus
properties.description: The Nucleus is an old submarine base owned by the United States Navy before the bombs fell. DiMA allowed the Church of the Children of Atom to utilize the place and, in return, protect his old memories from being accessed.

properties.name: Outcast Outpost
properties.description: The Outcast outpost (or VSS Facility) is a small Brotherhood Outcast compound located in a relatively clean pre-War military bunker. The building itself was under construction, with only the superstructure, elevator, and the VSS Bunker completed.

properties.name: Council Hall
properties.description:
The Council Hall is the government district of the capital of the New California Republic.
The district is centred around a plaza with the statue of the Vault Dweller, flanked by the Hall of Congress and the Presidential Mansion.

properties.name: Westin Ranch
properties.description: Westin Ranch is a large, private residence of Councilman Roger Westin, located in the western part of Shady Sands.

properties.name: University Point
properties.description: University Point was a settlement that was wiped out by the Institute synths in the year 2285. Formerly the pre-War Massachusetts Bay University

properties.name: Nuka-World transit center
properties.description: Lying west of the Lonely Chapel, the Nuka-World transit center has been a hub for guests of the Nuka-World amusement park. After arriving here, guests could park their cars and use the monorail to get to the park itself.
